<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Squat-To-Overhead-Press">Squat-To-Overhead Press</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/squat-to-overhead-press" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">squat-to-overhead press</a> is a full-body exercise that targets the quads, glutes, shoulders, and core. It’s an ideal compound movement for building strength and improving coordination. This exercise combines a lower-body squat with an upper-body press, making it an efficient workout for multiple muscle groups.</p>



<p>It’s a great way to improve functional strength, as the movement mimics everyday actions like lifting and carrying. Incorporating this exercise into your routine helps develop power and endurance across your entire body.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="50661201-Dumbbell-Squat-to-Overhead-Press_Thighs_" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/962979132?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Squat-To-Overhead Press Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold dumbbells at shoulder height with your elbows bent and palms facing each other.</li>



<li>Lower into a squat, making sure your knees track in line with your feet.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Push through your heels to stand, then press the dumbbells overhead.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height and repeat.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid arching your back during the overhead press to protect your spine.</li>



<li>Keep your weight in your heels during the squat to maintain balance and more effectively engage the hamstrings and glutes.</li>



<li>Press the dumbbells overhead in a straight line, avoiding flaring elbows.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



