<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Goblet-Squat">Dumbbell Goblet Squat</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-goblet-squat" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell goblet squat</a> targets the quads, glutes, and hamstrings. It’s a beginner-friendly exercise that improves lower-body strength and stability. Holding a dumbbell in front of your chest helps maintain an upright posture, making it easier to perform squats with proper form.</p>



<p>Additionally, it works well as a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-ab-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell ab workout</a>. The movement requires significant <a href="https://sportsmedicine-open.springeropen.com/articles/10.1186/s40798-018-0150-3" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">core engagement</a> to stabilize the body. This is especially true when transitioning from the squat to the overhead press, making it effective for <a href="https://europepmc.org/article/NBK/nbk551649" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">abdominal</a> activation.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Goblet Squat" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/976163588?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Goblet Squat Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell close to your chest.</li>



<li>Lower into a squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees.</li>



<li>Keep your chest lifted and your knees tracking over your toes.</li>



<li>Push through your heels to stand back up.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core tight to maintain balance and correct posture.</li>



<li>Don’t allow your knees to cave in. These should move straight in the direction of your toes.</li>



<li>Keep the dumbbell close to your chest to prevent leaning forward.</li>



<li>Ensure your heels stay flat on the ground throughout the movement.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



